AU  - Irvine, I. J.
T1  - The Use of Cross-Section Microdata in Life Cycle Models: An Application to Inequality Theory in Nonstationary Economies*
PY  - 1981
Y1  - 1981/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/1882392
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 96
IS  - 2
SP  - 301
EP  - 316
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper examines the appropriate use of cross-section microdata in life cycle models. Drawing upon recent empirical work based upon panel data, we illustrate how these results can be used as priors to generate a distribution of life cycle earnings. Such a surrogate distribution can be shown to possess the same properties as actual distributions. We focus attention particularly upon the treatment of economic growth and the unobservable components of earnings. In the final section of the paper, we show how such distributions might be used in inequality analysis.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1882392
