T1  - The Duality of a Dynamic Model of Equilibrium and an Optimal Growth Model: The Heterogeneous Capital Goods Case*
PY  - 1981
Y1  - 1981/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/1882391
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 96
IS  - 2
SP  - 271
EP  - 300
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The equivalence between optimal growth solutions and solutions of decentralized models of intertemporal allocation is explored in a one-consumer, heterogeneous capital goods framework. The decentralized economy follows a perfect foresight path. The main result is that the decentralized economy will impose on itself a transversality condition. This yields the interpretation of equilibrium prices as prices consistent with a certainty version of the efficient markets hypothesis. The results rest on the recent contribution by Benveniste and Scheinkman providing sufficient conditions for infinite horizon concave programs to exhibit capital value transversality as a necessary condition for optimality.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1882391
